Well done France, who could potentially be fantastic in the near future.

snippet.textDisplay:
Really good game. I had tipped the French and Welsh to do well this 6 Nations, but this French side were hugely underestimated by the English and they got hammered for it.


I think France are going to be the real deal come the next World Cup. I think France are better than England and they have just needed to have the right Management in place and now look at them beginning to come up. I hope it is not a one off, because I genuinely believe this is the French side that rises, dispatches the likes of England and NZ again and be at their best.



England looked rubbish in all honesty, for most of the game. Labored, no continuity, not a lot happening. The win past my team the All-Blacks in the World Cup does not give you complete autonomy in thinking you can now go on and beat everyone England, because it does not work like that. As much as I respect that win past NZ, ultimately, some English thought they have become the Worlds best and can beat any team, aint that right?. We all know that is what many English thought, and well they got it wrong again.


Wales or France are going to win this years 6 Nations, which is what I had predicted months back. Scotland and Ireland look very labored and boring, with England obviously with depth issues, which again is no real surprise and Italy are just plain awful.

snippet.textDisplay:
Lawes is a super second row, is he a blindside flanker? No! Curry is a kamikadze kid as a flanker, is he a n8? No! Both of these players are monsters on their nominal positions but they can't handle the versatility. Jones should have called up Dombrandt at n8, but he's a stubborn, self-assured and an overconfident coach. If he has Billy at n8, he lets the man play 80 minutes straight every game. But when Billy's injured, he always refuses the call up to the real n8 replacement whether it be Dombrandt or Simmonds.
One more thing, don't talk shit before the game cause you never know the outcome. France just hammered England in every aspect of the game, it were the Frenchmen who really showed the England team the brutality that Jones promised them before the game.

snippet.textDisplay: El Estadio de Francia en la ciudad de París Francia, la Selección Inglesa de Rugby (Los XV de la Rosa Roja) se enfrentan a la Selección Francesa de Rugby (Los Azules) en este doloroso Domingo en el Torneo de Rugby Guinness de las 6 Naciones. Los XV de la Rosa Roja, no pudieron de ser los héroes en la Copa Mundial de Rugby Japón 2019 contra la Selección Sudafricana de Rugby (Los Springboks) por ser Tri-Campeones. Pero el partido comienza cuando el Try fue anotado por Vincent Rattez y la conversión fue para Romain Ntamack. Pero el mismo Romain Ntamack anota un penalti con tres puntos para opacar a los XV de la Rosa Roja, a los Azules. El Try fue para Charles Ollivon y la segunda conversión fue para Romain Ntamack. Charles Ollivon anota un segundo Try y la tercera conversión fue por Romain Ntamack. El Try fue por Jonny May y la conversión, era de Owen Farrell para darle dos veces al marcador. Sin embargo, el penalti era de Owen Farrell pero no tuvieron tiempo de ganar al cuadro francés. El resultado fue muy doloroso por mi equipo favorito por un peor inicio. Francia 24✔-17 Inglaterra. En la próxima ronda, sera contra la Selección Italiana de Rugby (Los Azzurri) y la Selección Escocesa de Rugby (Los XV del Cardo). #RickyLovesThe6NationsRugby #In6NationsRugbyWeTrust #RickyLovesTheRugby #InRugbyWeTrust #RickyLovesTheRugbyUnion #InRugbyUnionWeTrust #SixNationsRugby🏉.
